OL,3,CIsolation heightens 'threat vigilance'
OL,4,Cin teenagers, study suggests
OL,6,F"Our experiment suggests that periods
OL,7,Fof isolation in adolescents might
OL,8,Fincrease their vulnerability to the
OL,9,Fdevelopment of anxiety, even when they
OL,10,Fare connected virtually."
OL,12,FIn the study, researchers set out to
OL,13,Finduce loneliness in teenagers and
OL,14,Fstudy the effects through a series of
OL,15,Ftests, including electrodes that
OL,16,Fmeasure sweat.
