OL,3,CIsolation heightens 'threat vigilance'
OL,4,Cin teenagers, study suggests
OL,6,FThis alertness can cause people to
OL,7,Ffeel anxious and uneasy.
OL,9,FOn average across the study, threat
OL,10,Fresponses were 70% higher after the
OL,11,Fisolation sessions, regardless of
OL,12,Fwhether participants had been
OL,13,Finteracting digitally.
OL,15,FThe scientists say this isolation and
OL,16,Floneliness might lead to something
OL,17,Fcalled excessive threat vigilance,
OL,18,Fwhich could negatively impact
OL,19,Fadolescent mental health over time.
