OL,3,CIsolation heightens 'threat vigilance'
OL,4,Cin teenagers, study suggests
OL,6,FThe authors suggest it could also
OL,7,Fcontribute to the persistent and
OL,8,Fexaggerated fear responses typical of
OL,9,Fanxiety disorders on the rise among
OL,10,Fyoung people around the world.
OL,12,FDr Livia Tomova, co-senior author and
OL,13,Flecturer in psychology at Cardiff
OL,14,FUniversity, who conducted the work
OL,15,Fwhile at Cambridge, said: "Loneliness
OL,16,Famong adolescents around the world has
OL,17,Fnearly doubled in recent years.
