OL,3,CIsolation heightens 'threat vigilance'
OL,4,Cin teenagers, study suggests
OL,6,F"The need for social interaction is
OL,7,Fespecially intense during adolescence,
OL,8,Fbut it is not clear whether online
OL,9,Fsocialising can fulfil this need.
OL,11,F"This study has shown that digital
OL,12,Finteractions might not mitigate some
OL,13,Fof the deep-rooted effects that
OL,14,Fisolation appears to have on
OL,15,Fteenagers."
OL,17,FThe findings are published in the
OL,18,Fjournal Royal Society Open Science.
